<article>
  <div class="article-header">
    <h1>Waterboro, ME Dispensary Guide</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Medical cannabis in Waterboro, Maine — Joey Nugz and The Garden serve York County patients</p>
  </div>

  <section class="fact-box">
    <h2>Waterboro at a Glance</h2>
    <table aria-label="Waterboro cannabis market overview">
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Fact</th><th scope="col">Details</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Dispensaries in Town</strong></td><td>2 — Joey Nugz, The Garden (both medical only)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Opt-In Status</strong></td><td>NOT OPTED IN — Medical only, no adult-use recreational</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Type</strong></td><td>Medical only (MMMP patients with valid card)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Nearest Recreational</strong></td><td>Biddeford or Sanford (~15-20 min)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Population</strong></td><td>~7,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>County</strong></td><td>York County</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Waterboro is one of the larger towns in York County, with approximately 7,800 residents. Despite its relatively substantial population, Waterboro has not opted in to adult-use cannabis retail — a decision that limits local recreational options while leaving the medical market to develop organically under the Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Program.</p>
    <p>Two medical cannabis operations have established themselves in Waterboro: Joey Nugz and The Garden. This is a notably higher number of medical operations than in comparable-sized towns, suggesting either strong patient demand or favorable local conditions for medical cannabis businesses.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Medical Cannabis Operations in Waterboro</h2>

    <h3>Joey Nugz (Medical)</h3>
    <p><strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 432-8863</p>
    <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.joeynugz207.com">joeynugz207.com</a></p>
    <p><strong>Hours:</strong> Appointment-based — 24-hour notice preferred, same-day available upon availability. Call to schedule.</p>
    <p>Joey Nugz is a medical cannabis dispensary in Waterboro that has built its brand around having what they describe as "the largest menu of medical marijuana in Maine." Their motto — "Come for the weed, stay for the vibe" — suggests a dispensary experience that emphasizes both product selection and customer atmosphere. They are an owner-operated, cash-only establishment.</p>
    <p>The breadth of their menu differentiates them in a market where many dispensaries offer more limited selections. For patients with specific needs or those seeking variety, Joey Nugz's extensive menu can be a significant draw.</p>
    <div class="deals-box">
      <h3>Joey Nugz Weekly Deals</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Indoor Flower:</strong> $100–$150/oz</li>
        <li><strong>Outdoor Flower:</strong> $50/oz</li>
        <li><strong>All Dabz:</strong> $15–$20</li>
        <li><strong>Full 1g Carts:</strong> $20</li>
        <li><strong>Monday–Wednesday:</strong> Specials on indoor/outdoor flower</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>The Garden (Medical — MMMP Caregiver)</h3>
    <p>The Garden operates as an MMMP caregiver, providing premium marijuana products to registered medical cannabis patients. The caregiver model means a more personalized approach to patient care, often with smaller-batch, hand-crafted products compared to larger dispensary operations. <strong>Contact information not publicly confirmed</strong> — verify via <a href="https://weedmaps.com/deliveries/in/united-states/maine/waterboro">Weedmaps</a> or the <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/open-data/adult-use/licensee-search">Maine OCP licensee search</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Payment Note:</strong> Cash only.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Nearest Recreational Dispensaries to Waterboro</h2>
    <p>Adult-use cannabis consumers in Waterboro must travel approximately 15–20 minutes to reach the nearest recreational dispensaries, which are in Biddeford and Sanford. The concentration of recreational options in Biddeford (four dispensaries) makes it the primary adult-use destination for the greater Waterboro area.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Town Status & Opt-In</h2>
    <p>Waterboro has <strong>not opted in</strong> to adult-use cannabis retail. No recreational cannabis establishments can operate within Waterboro town limits. Medical cannabis continues to operate under the MMMP framework.</p>
    <p>For current opt-in status and any municipal changes, refer to our <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-opt-in-tracker">Maine Cannabis Opt-In Tracker</a>.</p>
  </section>

